Outlier Elimination

We want to eliminate erratic behaviour of our productivity time series as witnessed in the previous analysis (LINK). To this end, I propose the following simple algorithm:

  • For each productivity time series (i.e.country/sector combination) calculate mean and standard deviation.
  • Identify outliers to be bigger than \(\tau\)-times the standard deviation of the (normalised) series. In the example below we set \(\tau = 2\) and illustrate this cut-off value by a dashed black line.
  • Drop all resp. outlier observations and run an \(MA(p)\) process over the reduced data set. In the example below we set \(p = 5\) to smooth over the business cycle. I highlight this series below in green.
  • Replace the outliers in the raw data series (highlighted below in red) with their counterparts of the \(MA\) estimates. This is how I generate the black series below.
